main event: On 11 September 1950, a Coast Guard photographer captured four photographs during a total eclipse of the Sun in Adak, Alaska.
interesting points: The sighting lasted about 6 minutes, The photographs revealed unidentified images that were not noticed at the time of exposure, There is a strong possibility that the unidentified images are lens flare due to overexposure for sun brightness, The event coincided with a total solar eclipse observed from the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Northwind, The photographs were discovered almost two years later upon development.
witness description: Electronic Technician in the U.S. Coast Guard
